# pa-framework public repo: whitelist-style exclude file.
# Default: ignore EVERY top-level entry. Then un-ignore the substrate paths.

/*

# Re-include public substrate at the root
!/.gitignore
!/.gitignore-public
!/.github/
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/docs/
!/examples/
!/pa/
!/projects/

# Inside projects/: ignore everything except the public-facing subtrees
projects/*
!projects/telegram-bot/
!projects/daily-mail-brief/
!projects/google-oauth-redirect/

# Inside pa/: exclude personal/build/private artifacts
pa/data/
pa/.claude-needs-brain
pa/dist/
pa/node_modules/
pa/src/oracle_agent.py
pa/src/active_mail.py
pa/src/learn_agent.py
pa/src/travel_butler.py
pa/src/gmail_utils.py
pa/src/telegram_notify.py
# Python tests for the excluded modules above — they import learn_agent/
# telegram_notify, which don't exist in the public mirror (permanently-broken
# tests there), and their fixtures/docstrings reference personal context.
pa/src/tests/
pa/scripts/upload_apk.py
# pa/scripts/upload_plan.py — INCLUDED (refactored to env-driven via PA_PLANS_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID; see Cat E3)

# Inside projects/telegram-bot/: exclude build/state/runtime artifacts + personal prompt
projects/telegram-bot/dist/
projects/telegram-bot/node_modules/
# Compiled .js artifacts that belong in dist/, not src/ (catches accidental tsc output in source dirs)
projects/telegram-bot/src/*.js
projects/telegram-bot/src/tests/*.js
projects/telegram-bot/.claude-needs-brain
projects/telegram-bot/bot-instructions.md
projects/telegram-bot/run-bot-hidden.vbs
projects/telegram-bot/test_repro.mjs

# Inside projects/daily-mail-brief/: track only scripts + README + requirements
projects/daily-mail-brief/*
!projects/daily-mail-brief/README.md
!projects/daily-mail-brief/requirements.txt
!projects/daily-mail-brief/scripts/
# Exclude personal one-off email helpers (hardcoded recipient/subject/body)
projects/daily-mail-brief/scripts/draft_reply.py

# Universal noise excludes
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/venv/
**/.venv/
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# === Repo hygiene patterns (mirror of private .gitignore — see docs/CONVENTIONS.md) ===
# Scratch and WIP — never tracked publicly
**/scratch/
**/temp_*.py
**/temp_*.json
**/temp_*.md
**/temp_*.txt
**/debug_*.py
**/debug_*.log
**/*-debug.log
**/test_repro.*
**/test_real_login.*

# LLM-agentic scratch writes at repo root (see private .gitignore for detail)
/message_to_user.md
/output.json
/skill_proposals.json

# Project data subdirectories (each project keeps its own data outside the repo)
**/data/raw/
**/data/processed/
**/data/exports/
